===Pre roll drops===
A gem table rolls before the main drop table.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1227166090603778048|date=11 February 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/nPo1I|archivedate=27 November 2020|quote=It adds a gem roll before each ore roll, and if you receive a gem you don't get the ore roll.}} There's a chance to receive nothing here so that players can receive no items from a rock even if they are guaranteed to receive an ore in the main drop table.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1280254444513435648|date=6 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/8Njmu|archivedate=27 November 2020|quote=Yes, [the mining gem table has] got [...] chance of giving no gem.}} The table gets more likely to be rolled if the player has an [[amulet of glory]] equipped: the probability grows from 1/256 to 1/86.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/830809149210521601|date=7 Feb 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/2BaHv|archivedate=18 Jun 2019|quote=[the actual increase when wearing the Amulet of Glory while mining is] 1/86 rather than 1/256 for a gem.}}

